- "Most recently published" refers to the latest posts based on their publication date;
- "Engagement leaderboard" refers to the posts with the highest engagement scores;
- "Attracted" refers to the number of comments received by the posts.

- 'Captivating' refers to posts with the highest engagement scores;
- 'Adorned with their associated tags' means including the tags linked to these posts;
- 'Details of their creators' include the usernames and email addresses of the users who created the posts.

- 'Top 10 most viewed' means the posts with the highest number of views;
- 'Engagement scores' are a measure of how much users interact with the post;
- 'Average time spent' refers to the average duration users spend on a post;
- 'Comment counts' represent the number of comments each post has received;
- 'Average comment time' is the average timestamp of when comments were made;
- 'Rank by popularity' involves ranking posts based on multiple metrics: views, engagement score, and time spent.

- "Latest" refers to the most recently published posts;
- "User engagement metrics" include average engagement score, views, and time spent by user;
- "Tags" are keywords or labels associated with a post.

- 'Shining stars in a vast galaxy' refers to the most engaging posts in the database;
- 'Captured the attention' means the posts have more than 100 views;
- 'Engagement score over 50' indicates a high level of user interaction and interest.
